to give you a few more not to.

273
00:16:33,852 --> 00:16:35,273
You know I'm innocent.

274
00:16:35,596 --> 00:16:38,020
- Yeah, probably.
- And yet you don't care.

275
00:16:38,053 --> 00:16:41,080
I don't care about anything other
than getting my life back, no.

276
00:16:41,447 --> 00:16:43,033
Your wife know who you really are?

277
00:16:43,883 --> 00:16:45,112
Yeah, you know how it is.

278
00:16:45,146 --> 00:16:47,903
Good men doing bad things
because of circumstance.

279
00:16:49,265 --> 00:16:50,736
I'd call her back if I were you.

280
00:16:50,829 --> 00:16:52,802
Tell her to forget you were ever born.

281
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:54,824
You would, would you?

282
00:16:55,231 --> 00:16:57,589
Stop the cancer from your life
spreading to theirs.

283
00:16:59,436 --> 00:17:00,815
Cancer of my life...

284
00:17:02,479 --> 00:17:04,359
I wouldn't be begging her to meet me

285
00:17:04,409 --> 00:17:06,854
in this third world dump
if it weren't for you and your life.

286
00:17:07,189 --> 00:17:08,559
There's no way out of this.

287
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:10,112
For you...

288
00:17:10,573 --> 00:17:11,725
or for any of us.

289
00:17:15,701 --> 00:17:17,035
For me there is.

290
00:17:18,534 --> 00:17:19,754
For me there is.

291
00:17:26,163 --> 00:17:27,684
How much of it have you spent?

292
00:17:27,829 --> 00:17:29,250
100,000...

293
00:17:30,779 --> 00:17:33,554
200,000. Of course, here,
it'd be more like a million.

294
00:17:33,644 --> 00:17:36,341
Be Louis XIV on a sum like that.

295
00:17:36,491 --> 00:17:38,279
The Sun King of Panama.

296
00:17:38,664 --> 00:17:40,825
You ain't gonna be seeing much sun now.

297
00:17:41,917 --> 00:17:43,237
I don't know.

298
00:17:45,953 --> 00:17:47,685
You know, Bagwell,

299
00:17:48,324 --> 00:17:49,879
out of all the guys,

300
00:17:50,363 --> 00:17:53,655
all eight of 'em, you were the guy
I was hoping would go down

301
00:17:53,656 --> 00:17:55,510
in a blaze of gunfire.

302
00:17:55,663 --> 00:17:58,097
Why don't you give me your best shot.
Finish the job.

303
00:17:58,471 --> 00:17:59,774
Maybe I will.

304
00:18:03,477 --> 00:18:06,285
That Siamese cat smile
just makes me want

305
00:18:06,335 --> 00:18:07,856
to open you up that much more.

306
00:18:08,708 --> 00:18:09,745
It's Cheshire.

307
00:18:09,845 --> 00:18:11,634
Cheshire cat smile.

308
00:18:12,904 --> 00:18:13,907
<i>Señor</i> Bellick?

309
00:18:15,806 --> 00:18:16,875
I'm free?

310
00:18:25,077 --> 00:18:26,827
What the hell's this?

311
00:18:26,905 --> 00:18:28,446
Hey, wait... wait a minute!

312
00:18:28,524 --> 00:18:29,725
What about him?

313
00:18:29,830 --> 00:18:31,535
He's the one that did it!

314
00:18:34,452 --> 00:18:35,939
<i>"Buena suerte,"</i> what's that mean?

315
00:18:38,942 --> 00:18:40,922
- <i>Buena suerte?</i>- Good luck.

316
00:19:11,062 --> 00:19:13,101
Where is she, Bellick?

317
00:19:14,357 --> 00:19:15,560
Where is she?

318
00:19:21,977 --> 00:19:23,431
Where's Maricruz?

319
00:19:23,564 --> 00:19:26,834
You wanna know where she is?
Find a way to get me out of this!

320
00:19:27,347 --> 00:19:28,874
Get me out of here!

321
00:19:29,108 --> 00:19:31,590
Sucre, get me out of this !
Get me out!

322
00:20:57,867 --> 00:20:59,488
Michael, that's a beautiful boat.

323
00:21:00,515 --> 00:21:03,148
Just promise me you'll change
the name when you take it.

324
00:21:03,213 --> 00:21:05,396
I don't think my mother
would have approved of you.

325
00:21:05,458 --> 00:21:06,578
Consider it done.

326
00:21:06,829 --> 00:21:07,832
Come on.

327
00:21:08,182 --> 00:21:09,185
Uncuff me.

328
00:21:09,229 --> 00:21:10,365
No, not yet.

329
00:21:10,410 --> 00:21:12,716
So is this the part
where you go back on your word?

330
00:21:13,418 --> 00:21:14,438
Hands up. Hands up.

331
00:21:19,900 --> 00:21:21,388
And as of now,

332
00:21:22,290 --> 00:21:23,729
