333
00:21:24,312 --> 00:21:25,315
Why?

334
00:21:27,412 --> 00:21:28,715
That's a good question.

335
00:21:29,183 --> 00:21:31,690
Figure it out someday on your own time.
Where's the money?

336
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,216
Cut him loose.

337
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:36,659
Come on, Alex, you already got the boat.

338
00:21:36,663 --> 00:21:37,758
Show a little good faith.

339
00:21:37,759 --> 00:21:38,786
The money.

340
00:21:39,579 --> 00:21:40,582
I want...

341
00:21:43,707 --> 00:21:45,472
-  Yeah.
- <i>I'm here. Where are you?</i>

342
00:21:45,826 --> 00:21:47,731
I'm inside the warehouse.

343
00:21:49,354 --> 00:21:50,360
I'll be right there.

344
00:21:57,162 --> 00:21:58,165
Here we go.

345
00:22:01,591 --> 00:22:02,644
Hello. <i>Hola.</i>

346
00:22:03,730 --> 00:22:06,006
- You speak English?
- <i>Yes, sir. Can I help you?</i>

347
00:22:06,044 --> 00:22:08,410
Yes, yes. Mira Flores Docks.

348
00:22:08,411 --> 00:22:09,709
<i>Is everything alright?</i>
- Yes.

349
00:22:09,826 --> 00:22:10,845
There's been a murder.

350
00:22:10,879 --> 00:22:11,879
<i>Are you in distress?</i>

351
00:22:11,913 --> 00:22:14,402
A well-dressed Asian man's
just been shot by two Americans.

352
00:22:14,497 --> 00:22:16,623
- <i>We'll send a car right away, sir.</i>
- Yes, come.

353
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:22,616
So you kill him and frame us.

354
00:22:23,746 --> 00:22:24,749
Why?

355
00:22:26,576 --> 00:22:27,761
So everyone

356
00:22:28,214 --> 00:22:29,483
will leave me

357
00:22:29,952 --> 00:22:30,981
alone!

358
00:22:31,627 --> 00:22:33,106
'Cause that's all I want.

359
00:22:33,762 --> 00:22:35,317
That... and the money.

360
00:22:35,558 --> 00:22:37,213
It's not gonna happen, Alex.

361
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:39,389
- Let him go.
- Give me the money.

362
00:22:39,427 --> 00:22:41,115
- Let him go.
- Give me the money!

363
00:22:54,230 --> 00:22:55,676
I am dumbfounded.

364
00:23:02,930 --> 00:23:04,217
Don't be shy.

365
00:23:05,650 --> 00:23:06,920
They're all yours.

366
00:23:09,315 --> 00:23:11,500
You said you'd have them
right where we wanted them.

367
00:23:11,534 --> 00:23:13,169
This isn't right where we want them.

368
00:23:14,149 --> 00:23:15,152
Well...

369
00:23:15,587 --> 00:23:17,241
That's your job now.

370
00:23:19,168 --> 00:23:20,773
This is as far as I go.

371
00:23:22,416 --> 00:23:23,903
Or is it something else?

372
00:23:25,432 --> 00:23:26,688
Another reason we're all here.

373
00:23:27,373 --> 00:23:28,376
Like that.

374
00:23:30,678 --> 00:23:32,164
- Like a double-cross.
- Yeah.

375
00:23:32,165 --> 00:23:34,017
Just like that. Say good-bye.

376
00:23:36,601 --> 00:23:38,207
Like minds think alike!

377
00:23:38,892 --> 00:23:40,079
Hey, Alex!

378
00:25:05,749 --> 00:25:08,728
Once seated, your four-piece
will be mounted to the floor mount.

379
00:25:08,943 --> 00:25:10,932
During transport,
do not speak to either I...

380
00:25:10,982 --> 00:25:12,135
I know the drill.

381
00:25:16,215 --> 00:25:17,251
Get in.

382
00:25:40,979 --> 00:25:42,684
So, what do we got, another 30 minutes?

383
00:25:42,957 --> 00:25:44,595
Yeah, something like that.

384
00:25:44,678 --> 00:25:46,199
Why didn't you take the freeway?

385
00:25:46,316 --> 00:25:47,453
Rush hour.

386
00:25:50,093 --> 00:25:51,815
- Hell.
- What?

387
00:25:52,264 --> 00:25:53,833
The engine light just came on.

388
00:25:54,034 --> 00:25:56,090
It just got serviced at motor pool.

389
00:25:57,380 --> 00:25:59,369
We'd better pull over just to make sure.

390
00:26:14,749 --> 00:26:16,253
All right, I'll check it out.

391
00:26:24,714 --> 00:26:27,037
In the French Resistance,
it was considered a high honor

392
00:26:27,100 --> 00:26:28,485
to face a Nazi firing squad.

393
00:26:28,519 --> 00:26:31,229
- I thought I told you to be quiet.
- Meant, you did your job.

394
00:26:32,548 --> 00:26:35,180
The highest honor was to smile
when they shot you.

395
00:26:38,449 --> 00:26:39,518
Took you long enough.

396
00:26:52,447 --> 00:26:54,537
Lake Gatun, Eastern Canal,

397
00:26:54,637 --> 00:26:56,074
approaches to Cartagena.

398
00:26:56,158 --> 00:26:57,394
$27.50

399
00:26:57,762 --> 00:26:59,318
What's that crossing take?

400
00:26:59,537 --> 00:27:02,478
Two days if you're under
full sail all the time.

401
00:27:02,645 --> 00:27:05,092
Good time of you to be down here.
No storms, nothing.

402
00:27:05,245 --> 00:27:06,615
Had enough storms recently.

403
00:27:07,501 --> 00:27:09,991
Enjoy it. It's a beautiful crossing.

404
00:27:10,242 --> 00:27:11,245
I plan to.

405
00:27:11,278 --> 00:27:12,314
This boat here,

406
00:27:12,365 --> 00:27:13,517
who's it belong to?

407
00:27:14,295 --> 00:27:15,298
<i>Señor?</i>

408
00:27:15,401 --> 00:27:18,034
We got a call that this boat
was used in some illegal trafficking.

409
00:27:18,104 --> 00:27:21,534
It's the wrong boat, pal.
You can check it if you want to, but...

410
00:27:22,165 --> 00:27:24,736
- Hey, you can't just...
- This is Panama, friend.

411
00:27:25,431 --> 00:27:26,985
Get acquainted with the law, huh?

412
00:27:30,866 --> 00:27:31,869
I...

413
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:38,067
Yes, I definitely think
you need to get acquainted.

414
00:27:38,266 --> 00:27:39,268
Chico!

415
00:27:52,599 --> 00:27:53,767
You think they got him?

416
00:27:53,833 --> 00:27:54,967
It's a pretty singular boat.

417
00:27:55,498 --> 00:27:57,267
That's a lot of coke
to be carrying around.

418
00:27:57,334 --> 00:27:58,480
If you're at the helm, man...

419
00:27:58,481 --> 00:28:00,798
You'll doing some serious time.
Ten years minimum.

420
00:28:00,898 --> 00:28:01,901
Yeah, you would.

421
00:28:02,148 --> 00:28:03,335
We lost the boat.

422
00:28:03,847 --> 00:28:06,036
At least we got the dead man's money.

423
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,813
It's our ticket
to the rest of our lives,

424
00:28:07,863 --> 00:28:10,067
minus what I'm sending
Westmoreland's daughter.

425
00:28:10,748 --> 00:28:11,751
Hey.

426
00:28:13,466 --> 00:28:14,536
You showed up.

427
00:28:14,766 --> 00:28:15,785
We had a deal.

428
00:28:16,220 --> 00:28:17,373
This is my brother.

429
00:28:17,607 --> 00:28:19,267
- Hey.
- This way.

430
00:28:21,833 --> 00:28:22,933
So we get out of here,

431
00:28:23,259 --> 00:28:24,304
and we never look back.

432
00:28:24,997 --> 00:28:26,234
We never look back.

433
00:28:33,045 --> 00:28:35,318
I want to thank you, Michael,
for everything.

434
00:28:37,267 --> 00:28:38,467
You're welcome.

435
00:28:41,024 --> 00:28:43,467
It's the best I could do
with the money you gave me.

436
00:28:44,651 --> 00:28:45,670
That'll work.

437
00:28:52,592 --> 00:28:53,611
She's very pretty.

438
00:28:53,845 --> 00:28:55,552
She'll get us where we need to go,
right?

439
00:28:56,165 --> 00:28:57,317
Not the boat, señor.

440
00:29:22,631 --> 00:29:24,252
So, I got your message.

441
00:29:26,247 --> 00:29:27,985
Thank God, I found you guys.

442
00:29:31,513 --> 00:29:33,001
"Thank God" is right.

443
00:29:33,247 --> 00:29:34,902
Michael, Lincoln's free.

444
00:29:35,882 --> 00:29:36,893
What?

445
00:29:38,243 --> 00:29:39,663
It's all over the news.

446
00:29:39,780 --> 00:29:41,626
Paul Kellerman came forward.

447
00:29:42,548 --> 00:29:46,067
And he had... everything documented
and he made a full confession.

448
00:29:46,266 --> 00:29:47,902
- Are you serious?
- Yeah.

449
00:29:49,556 --> 00:29:51,813
- Everything?
- Everything, all charges.

450
00:30:03,565 --> 00:30:04,567
What...

451
00:30:05,136 --> 00:30:07,188
- No more...
- You don't have to run anymore.

452
00:30:11,829 --> 00:30:13,100
What about Michael?

453
00:30:15,751 --> 00:30:17,723
A friend of my father's
getting into it, but...

454
00:30:18,676 --> 00:30:20,857
he's pretty confident
that under the circumstances,

455
00:30:20,858 --> 00:30:22,564
nobody's going to pursue you on this.

456
00:30:28,284 --> 00:30:29,371
I need a drink.

457
00:30:31,298 --> 00:30:32,853
I'll go see what I can find.

458
00:30:51,330 --> 00:30:52,349
Here.

459
00:30:53,998 --> 00:30:55,419
Help me out of this.

460
00:31:02,034 --> 00:31:03,037
We did it, Linc.

461
00:31:06,046 --> 00:31:07,897
- We did it.
- Yeah.

462
00:31:11,268 --> 00:31:12,405
You almost did it.

463
00:31:19,893 --> 00:31:20,899
You want the money?

464
00:31:23,434 --> 00:31:24,446
Take the money.

465
00:31:24,530 --> 00:31:25,533
Take it.

466
00:31:26,481 --> 00:31:28,186
You think this is about the money?

467
00:31:31,161 --> 00:31:33,072
Pocket change like five million?

468
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:34,417
Then what is it about?

469
00:31:34,496 --> 00:31:36,250
My brother's been exonerated.

470
00:31:36,626 --> 00:31:37,813
The President stepped down.

471
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:39,919
We're not a threat anymore. It's over.

472
00:31:41,030 --> 00:31:42,501
You may be done with us,

473
00:31:42,835 --> 00:31:44,790
but that doesn't mean
we're done with you.

474
00:31:44,841 --> 00:31:46,261
The police are on their way.

475
00:31:46,295 --> 00:31:47,911
It started with me.

476
00:31:48,964 --> 00:31:50,134
Let my brother go.

477
00:31:50,318 --> 00:31:51,555
That's sweet.

478
00:31:52,190 --> 00:31:54,463
That's sweet.
You don't hear that much anymore,

479
00:31:54,580 --> 00:31:56,502
that sort of fidelity in families.

480
00:31:57,008 --> 00:31:59,636
Two brothers that'll go
to the ends of the earth for each other.

481
00:32:01,417 --> 00:32:03,230
Too bad only one of you survive.

482
00:32:03,815 --> 00:32:04,818
Don't!

483
00:32:17,063 --> 00:32:18,116
We got to go.

484
00:33:35,746 --> 00:33:37,459
My men are ordered to fire

485
00:33:37,563 --> 00:33:39,768
if you don't come out of there
with your hands first.

486
00:33:40,286 --> 00:33:41,556
Come on, come on.

487
00:33:45,718 --> 00:33:49,432
Murder is not something that we take
lightly here on Panamanian soil.

488
00:33:50,402 --> 00:33:53,457
So come on out of there,
and there will be no more death.

489
00:33:53,507 --> 00:33:54,944
Michael, I took a man's life.

490
00:33:56,398 --> 00:33:57,985
Don't think about that now.

491
00:33:58,729 --> 00:34:00,617
You and I have got a date, remember?

492
00:34:01,185 --> 00:34:03,825
Two limes and a couple of beers,
don't forget that.

493
00:34:03,842 --> 00:34:05,480
This is your last warning!

494
00:34:06,413 --> 00:34:07,499
Give me the gun.

495
00:34:10,758 --> 00:34:12,279
I took a man's life.

496
00:34:14,109 --> 00:34:16,023
We're going to walk out of here
together,

497
00:34:16,931 --> 00:34:18,953
